==Old English==
===Etymology===
A West Germanic word, of ultimately unknown origin.  Cognate with Middle Dutch ''[[haghetisse]]'' (Dutch ''[[heks]]''), Old High German ''[[hagzissa]]'' (German ''[[Hexe]]'').

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈhægtes:e/}}

